By Farmer Jimbo on Sunday, April 29, 2001 - 08:23 am:

From The Offsripng's "Americana"

Note: This is a modified CDD file. The CDD from the original disc is a two session file. This CDD has been modified to erase the traces of the second session. I have verified that a burned CD using this CDD does indeed produce a Worm/Worm with an extra 20 weeks lifespan and the "Roll Assult" tech in MR2.

By Quincunx on Monday, July 16, 2001 - 02:26 pm:

I can confirm the extra attack... and Roll Assault is nothing to be scoffed at (S/D/C/E). But it is just a Worm/Worm; even the icon next to the rank on the Monster Data screen is brown rather than the cyan ones that "regular" rares have.

Perhaps this is another monster like Lisa's Crazy Monol (the one with all 25s for stats); that is, not a traditional xxx/??? rare, but a unique monster triggered by a single CD, possibly either as a reference to test the software, or as a joke or an Easter egg.

Regardless, I'm just glad to have another Worm (and a pure one at that) in my collection. I attempted the Beaclon unlocking with a Worm/Pixie, the only Worm I had out of 260+ CDs, and was foiled by Loyalty problems. So thanks, Farmer Jimbo!
